LEAD C: TOURNAMENT COMPOSITION
  Given tournaments T1 on {1,...,a} and T2 on {1,...,b},
  define T1[v <- T2]: replace vertex v with T2.
  All arcs from T2 to T1\v get direction from v's arcs.
  QUESTION: H(T1[v <- T2]) = f(H(T1), H(T2), v)?
======================================================================

  Testing LEXICOGRAPHIC PRODUCT: T1 lex T2
  Vertices (i,j), arc rule: i1->i2 in T1, OR (i1=i2 and j1->j2 in T2)

  3 lex 2: 16 products, H_prod / (H1 * H2^3) = [1.0, 15.0]
  H_prod / (H1 * H2) = [1.0, 15.0]

  2 lex 3: 16 products, H_prod / (H1 * H2^2) = [1.0]
  H_prod / (H1 * H2) = [1.0, 3.0]

