LEAD E: THE DELETION TOWER — H(T) → H(T-v) → H(T-v-w) → ...
  Delete vertices one by one. How does H evolve?
  Connection to the OCF: H(T) - H(T-v) = 2 * sum_C mu(C)
======================================================================

  bits=0, H(T)=1:
    Delete vertex 0: H(T-0) = 1, delta = 0
    Delete vertex 1: H(T-1) = 1, delta = 0
    Delete vertex 2: H(T-2) = 1, delta = 0
    Delete vertex 3: H(T-3) = 1, delta = 0
    Delete vertex 4: H(T-4) = 1, delta = 0
    R(T) = sum H(T-v) / H(T) = 5/1 = 5.0000
    n - R = 0.0000

  bits=42, H(T)=13:
    Delete vertex 0: H(T-0) = 3, delta = 10
    Delete vertex 1: H(T-1) = 3, delta = 10
    Delete vertex 2: H(T-2) = 5, delta = 8
    Delete vertex 3: H(T-3) = 5, delta = 8
    Delete vertex 4: H(T-4) = 5, delta = 8
    R(T) = sum H(T-v) / H(T) = 21/13 = 1.6154
    n - R = 3.3846

  bits=341, H(T)=15:
    Delete vertex 0: H(T-0) = 5, delta = 10
    Delete vertex 1: H(T-1) = 5, delta = 10
    Delete vertex 2: H(T-2) = 5, delta = 10
    Delete vertex 3: H(T-3) = 5, delta = 10
    Delete vertex 4: H(T-4) = 5, delta = 10
    R(T) = sum H(T-v) / H(T) = 25/15 = 1.6667
    n - R = 3.3333

  bits=682, H(T)=15:
    Delete vertex 0: H(T-0) = 5, delta = 10
    Delete vertex 1: H(T-1) = 5, delta = 10
    Delete vertex 2: H(T-2) = 5, delta = 10
    Delete vertex 3: H(T-3) = 5, delta = 10
    Delete vertex 4: H(T-4) = 5, delta = 10
    R(T) = sum H(T-v) / H(T) = 25/15 = 1.6667
    n - R = 3.3333

  bits=1023, H(T)=1:
